<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EC) No 2788/98 of 22 December 1998 amending Council Directive 70/524/EEC concerning additives in feedingstuffs as regards the withdrawal of authorisation for certain growth promoters </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 2788/98, millega muudetakse s&ouml;&ouml;dalisandeid k&auml;sitlevat n&otilde;ukogu direktiivi 70/524/EM&Uuml; seoses teatavate kasvustimulaatorite kasutusloa t&uuml;histamisega </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> 22. detsember 1998 EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Act of Accession of Austria, Finland and Sweden, and in particular Article 151 in conjunction with Annex XV, Title VII(E) (4) thereof, and to the amendments to the Treaties on which the European Union is founded, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Austria, Soome ja Rootsi &uuml;hinemisakti, eriti selle artiklit 151 seostatuna &uuml;hinemisakti XV lisa VII jaotise E osa l&otilde;ikega 4, ning Euroopa Liidu asutamislepingutes tehtud muudatusi, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Directive 70/524/EEC of 23 November 1970 concerning additives in feedingstuffs (1), as last amended by Commission Directive 98/19/EC (2), and in particular Article 11(3) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse s&ouml;&ouml;dalisandeid k&auml;sitlevat n&otilde;ukogu 23. novembri 1970. aasta direktiivi 70/524/EM&Uuml;, (1) viimati muudetud komisjoni direktiiviga 98/19/E&Uuml;, (2) eriti selle artikli 11 l&otilde;iget 3, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Sweden was authorised under Annex XV to the Act of Accession to maintain its legislation in force before accession until 31 December 1998 with regard to the prohibition of the use in feedingstuffs of additives belonging to the groups of growth promoters; whereas on 10 April 1997 and 2 February 1998 it submitted applications for adjustments in respect of carbadox and olaquindox, accompanied by detailed scientific reasoning; whereas the Commission is required to take a decision on the adjustment applications submitted by Sweden not later than 31 December 1998; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: Rootsil lubati &uuml;hinemisakti XV lisa alusel kuni 31. detsembrini 1998 j&auml;tta j&otilde;usse enne &uuml;hinemist kehtinud &otilde;igusaktid seoses kasvustimulaatorite r&uuml;hma kuuluvate s&ouml;&ouml;dalisandite kasutamise keelamisega; Rootsi esitas 10. aprillil 1997 ja 2. veebruaril 1998 karbadoksi ja olakvindoksi k&auml;sitlevad kohandamistaotlused koos &uuml;ksikasjalike teaduslike p&otilde;hjendustega; komisjon peab tegema Rootsi esitatud kohandamistaotluste kohta otsuse hiljemalt 31. detsembriks 1998; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, pursuant to Article 11 of Directive 70/524/EEC, a Member State which, as a result of new information or of a reassessment of existing information made since the provisions in question wee adopted, has detailed grounds for establishing that the use of one of the additives listed in the Directive constitutes a danger to animal or human health or the environment may temporarily suspend the authorisation to use that additive; </inglise>
<eesti> direktiivi 70/524/EM&Uuml; artikli 11 kohaselt v&otilde;ib liikmesriik ajutiselt k&otilde;nealuse s&ouml;&ouml;dalisandi kasutamise keelata, kui liikmesriigil on uue teabe v&otilde;i olemasoleva teabe &uuml;mberhindamise tulemusena p&auml;rast asjakohaste s&auml;tete vastuv&otilde;tmist &uuml;ksikasjalikud t&otilde;endid selle kohta, et m&otilde;ne direktiivis loetletud s&ouml;&ouml;dalisandi kasutamine on ohtlik loomade v&otilde;i inimeste tervisele v&otilde;i keskkonnale; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Kingdom of the Netherlands prohibited the use on its territory of carbadox in feedingstuffs on 6 September 1997; whereas it communicated the detailed grounds for that decision to the other Member States and the Commission on 18 July 1997; </inglise>
<eesti> Hollandi Kuningriik keelas 6. septembril 1997 karbadoksi kasutamise s&ouml;&ouml;tades oma territooriumil; Holland edastas selle otsuse &uuml;ksikasjalikud p&otilde;hjendused teistele liikmesriikidele ja komisjonile 18. juulil 1997; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas by virtue of Article 3a(b) of Directive 70/524/EEC authorisation of a substance is not to be given if, in view of its conditions of use, it has an adverse effect on human or animal health; </inglise>
<eesti> vastavalt direktiivi 70/524/EM&Uuml; artikli 3a punktile b ei anta luba aine kasutamiseks juhul, kui sellel on kasutamistingimusi silmas pidades kahjulik m&otilde;ju inimeste v&otilde;i loomade tervisele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Commission has consulted the Scientific Committee on Animal Nutrition (SCAN) on whether, based on the information given to the Commission, use of the quinoxaline-N-dioxides carbadox and olaquindox presented a risk to consumers, to operators or to the animal itself; </inglise>
<eesti> komisjon on pidanud s&ouml;&ouml;tade teaduskomiteega n&otilde;u selle &uuml;le, kas kinoksaliin-N-dioksiidide ehk karbadoksi ja olakvindoksi kasutamine on komisjonile edastatud teabe alusel tarbijatele, ettev&otilde;tjatele v&otilde;i loomadele ohtlik; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, having studied the information supplied to the Commission, SCAN noted in its opinion issued on 10 July 1998 that it was maintaining its previous opinions on the acceptability of the quinoxaline-N-dioxides carbadox and olaquindox, within their previously defined conditions of use; </inglise>
<eesti> p&auml;rast komisjoni esitatud teabega tutvumist sedastas s&ouml;&ouml;tade teaduskomitee oma 10. juulil 1998 avaldatud arvamuses, et j&auml;&auml;b oma varasemate arvamuste juurde, mille kohaselt kinoksaliin-N-dioksiidi v&otilde;ib kasutada varem m&auml;&auml;ratletud tingimustel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, however, SCAN has acknowledged that neither of these two substances has had an ideal safety profile in laboratory animal tests and that it is unlikely that other additives with such genotoxic properties will be developed in future; </inglise>
<eesti> s&ouml;&ouml;tade teaduskomitee on tunnistanud, et kummagi k&otilde;nealuse aine ohutusomadused ei osutunud laboratoorsetes loomkatsetes ideaalseks ning on t&otilde;en&auml;oline, et muid selliste genotoksiliste omadustega s&ouml;&ouml;dalisandeid edaspidi v&auml;lja ei t&ouml;&ouml;tata; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas SCAN acknowledged that carbadox was genotoxic and carcinogenic for rodents and that olaquindox was genotoxic and tumorigenic for rodents; </inglise>
<eesti> s&ouml;&ouml;tade teaduskomitee tunnistas, et karbadoksil oli n&auml;rilistele genotoksiline ja kantserogeenne m&otilde;ju ning olakvindoksil genotoksiline ja tumorigeenne m&otilde;ju; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas SCAN notes, and the Commission for its part fully agrees, that the possible exposure of workers is undoubtedly a risk, since they are exposed to the parent molecules; whereas individuals changing air filter mats in feed plants are at special genotoxic or carcinogenic risk following possible exposure through the skin or by inhalation; whereas the possibility of absorbing the parent substance by individuals exposed to the additives in the factory or on farm exists; </inglise>
<eesti> s&ouml;&ouml;tade teaduskomitee sedastab ja komisjon &uuml;hineb t&auml;ielikult komitee arvamusega, et t&ouml;&ouml;tajate v&otilde;imalik kokkupuude k&otilde;nealuste ainetega on kahtlemata ohtlik, kuna nad puutuvad kokku l&auml;htemolekulidega; genotoksiline ja kantserogeenne m&otilde;ju ohustab eriti isikud, kes vahetavad s&ouml;&ouml;datehastes &otilde;hufiltrikangast, kuna k&otilde;nealused ained v&otilde;ivad sattuda nende nahale v&otilde;i hingamisteedesse; l&auml;htemolekulid v&otilde;ivad sattuda s&ouml;&ouml;dalisanditega kokkupuutuvate inimeste organismi tehases v&otilde;i p&otilde;llumajandusettev&otilde;ttes; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas SCAN is aware that many conditions must be met before these substances can be safely used; whereas SCAN would like to know if these conditions are met in practice; whereas SCAN recommends in particular that exposure to carbadox and olaquindox in the workplace be re-evaluated and that epidemiological studies of the health status of additive-exposed workers be carried out; </inglise>
<eesti> s&ouml;&ouml;tade teaduskomitee on teadlik, et k&otilde;nealuste ainete ohutuks kasutamiseks tuleb t&auml;ita mitmeid tingimusi; s&ouml;&ouml;tade teaduskomitee soovib teada, kas neid tingimusi tegelikult t&auml;idetakse; s&ouml;&ouml;tade teaduskomitee soovitab, et tuleks &uuml;mber hinnata eriti t&ouml;&ouml;kohal toimuvad kokkupuuted karbadoksi ja olakvindoksiga ning et tuleks teha epidemioloogilisi uuringuid s&ouml;&ouml;dalisanditega kokkupuutuvate t&ouml;&ouml;tajate tervise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Commission, for its part, believes that it is not possible to set a threshold for a genotoxic additive below which it presents no risk to the consumer, since even a small quantity of residues of the additive can provoke a tumour-inducing mutation; whereas a time limit for withdrawal that will ensure consumer safety cannot therefore be fixed; Whereas the Commission believes that precise description of the composition of the preparations and recommendations to wear masks and protective clothing are not sufficient to guarantee the protection of operators at plant or farm level; whereas cases have indeed been reported to the Commission of livestock farmers who, lacking protection, have been exposed through inhalation or skin contact to the genotoxic and potentially carcinogenic parent substances; </inglise>
<eesti> komisjon on seisukohal, et genotoksilise s&ouml;&ouml;dalisandi puhul ei ole v&otilde;imalik m&auml;&auml;rata k&uuml;nnist, millest allpool selle kasutamine ei ohusta tarbijat, kuna isegi v&auml;ike kogus s&ouml;&ouml;dalisandi j&auml;&auml;ke v&otilde;ib p&otilde;hjustada kasvajaid tekitavaid mutatsioone; seet&otilde;ttu ei saa kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata s&ouml;&ouml;dalisandi kasutusloa tagasiv&otilde;tmise t&auml;htaega, mis tagaks tarbija ohutuse; komisjon on seisukohal, et valmististe koostise t&auml;psest kirjeldusest ja soovitustest kanda kaitsemaske ja -riietust ei piisa tehaste ja p&otilde;llumajandusettev&otilde;tete t&ouml;&ouml;tajate kaitse tagamiseks; komisjonile on teatatud karjakasvatajatest, kes on naha v&otilde;i hingamisteede kaudu olnud kokkupuutes genotoksiliste ja kantserogeensete l&auml;htemolekulidega; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in view of their possible adverse effect on human health, the authorisations for the growth promoters carbadox and olaquindox should be withdrawn; </inglise>
<eesti> kasvustimulaatorite karbadoksi ja olakvindoksi kasutusload tuleks tagasi v&otilde;tta, pidades silmas nende v&otilde;imalikku kahjulikku m&otilde;ju inimeste tervisele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Directive are in accordance with the opinion of the Standing Committee on Feedingstuffs, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolevas direktiivis etten&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las alalise s&ouml;&ouml;dakomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
